# v1.81.0 — Post-submit success confirmation popup

## M1 — Component built + smoke test wiring (DONE)

**Component:** [src/components/SuccessConfirmationModal.tsx](src/components/SuccessConfirmationModal.tsx)

**Prop API:**
```ts
interface Props {
  open: boolean
  title: string
  description?: string
  okHref: string          // absolute URL the OK button (and ESC + backdrop) navigate to
  onClose?: () => void    // fires on OK click, ESC, backdrop click
}
```

**Animation:** SVG check uses `pathLength={1}` + stroke-dasharray=1 +
stroke-dashoffset 1 → 0 over 0.45s `cubic-bezier(0.65, 0, 0.45, 1)` after a
0.18s delay. The ring scales from 0.6 → 1.0 with overshoot
(`cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)`) over 0.25s. Both keyframes live in
[src/app/globals.css](src/app/globals.css) so no new deps and no
inline-style issues.

**A11y:** `role="dialog"` + `aria-modal="true"` + `aria-labelledby`. Focus
trap + body scroll lock + Tab cycle inside the card + previously-focused
element restored on unmount, mirroring `SignInLightbox`. ESC closes
(equivalent to OK). Backdrop click closes (equivalent to OK). All four
exit affordances navigate to `okHref`.

**Surface tokens:** `bg-card` / `border-border-default` / `electric-green`
OK button / `font-display tracking-tight uppercase` heading — visually
sibling to the v1.80.8 `SignInLightbox` + `ApplyToLeagueModal`.

**Mount mechanism:** [src/components/SuccessConfirmationGate.tsx](src/components/SuccessConfirmationGate.tsx)
reads `useSearchParams()` and renders the modal when
`?submitted=<descriptor>` matches a known message in the `MESSAGES` map.
Mounted lazily inside [Dashboard.tsx](src/components/Dashboard.tsx) via
`dynamic(() => import('./SuccessConfirmationGate'), { loading: () => null })`
so the gate's chunk only fetches on the success path.

**Smoke test:** Will be added in M4 alongside the regression-target.

