## M3 — Pattern propagated, join paths surfaced as incompatible

**`registerToLeague`** — wired in M2 alongside `applyToLeague` (both
live in [src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts](src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts)).
The form on `/recruit/<slug>` passes
`originPath = \`/id/${leagueSlug}\`` as a hardcoded string rather than
capturing `window.location.pathname` because the route-level guard at
[src/app/recruit/[slug]/page.tsx:104](src/app/recruit/[slug]/page.tsx:104)
short-circuits a now-bound user back to `/id/<slug>` — pointing the
popup at `/recruit/<slug>` would re-bounce before the modal could mount.

### Join paths — out of scope (spec exception)

The spec said: **"If a path already redirects to a 'thank you' page or
has a different success UX, leave it alone — but document which ones."**
All 5 join-flow actions in
[src/app/join/[code]/actions.ts](src/app/join/[code]/actions.ts) fall
under that exception. Per-path notes:

| Action | Current redirect target | Why no popup |
|---|---|---|
| `redeemInvite` (skipOnboarding=true) | `/join/<code>/welcome` | `/welcome` IS the explicit thank-you page — `<h1>You're all set!</h1>` + binding-confirmation + "Go to {league}" CTA. Stacking a popup over it is redundant. |
| `redeemInvite` (skipOnboarding=false) | `/join/<code>/onboarding` | Continuation form. The user is mid-flow — popup at form mount would block them from filling out the very form they just navigated to. |
| `submitOnboarding` | `/join/<code>/id-upload` | Continuation form (per v1.35.0 PR η, name/position submit doesn't yet flip onboardingStatus to COMPLETED). Same blocking problem as above. |
| `submitIdUpload` | `/join/<code>/welcome` | `/welcome` thank-you page (final-step landing). |
| `skipIdUpload` | `/join/<code>/welcome` | Same — `/welcome` already does the thank-you. |
| `completeOnboardingWithId` | `/join/<code>/welcome` | Same — single-page onboarding's `/welcome` landing. |

**Going-back semantics is incompatible with multi-step join flow.** The
spec's "OK button directs the user back to the page where they
initiated the action" assumes a single-shot action whose origin is
visit-able after success. For join paths the origin is a partially-filled
form that the user has already finished with — sending them "back" to
`/join/<code>/onboarding` after `submitOnboarding` is anti-flow. The
recruiting paths fit the pattern cleanly (origin = `/id/<slug>`, which
naturally re-renders to State B "being reviewed"); the join paths
don't.

**Spec note (surfaced back):** if the orchestrator wants the popup
treatment on the join flow, the natural extension is to redirect to
`/welcome?submitted=onboardingComplete` and have `/welcome` render the
popup with `okHref="/id/<league.subdomain>"`. That replaces (rather
than overlays) the current welcome card. This is a separate UX decision
about whether the welcome card or the popup is the canonical
thank-you surface — out of scope for v1.81.0.

